  "description": "<p>分类: <a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/category/industry/\" rel=\"tag\">产业新闻</a></p><div style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/2013/11/05/canadian-government-blocked-potential-lenovo-bid-for-blackberry/\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://hss-prod.hss.aol.com/hss/storage/adam/7e7a41ee5ef0120108962cc4fe4907e6/heinsbbresults.jpg\" /></a></div>\n\n<div><br />\n根据 The Globe and Mail 最新的报道来看，如果没有加拿大政府出手干预的话，BlackBerry 今天可能已经归于<a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/2013/10/18/lenovo-blackberry-bid/\">联想</a>名下了。据知情人士透露，加拿大政府担心联想潜在的收购会影响到国家安全，因为 BlackBerry 的许多业务都是和加拿大的通讯基础设施有关的。<br />\n<br />\n据称联想对收购诚意十足，但政府的影响力实在太大，以致于 BlackBerry 这边都没有递交表达意向的正式提议。话说后者当时正处于急需对策来止住颓势的阶段，对他们来说悬而未决的收购应该只会有害无益吧。但这一切放到现在已经不重要了，因为 BlackBerry 已经<a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/2013/11/04/blackberry-abandons-fairfax-deal-heins-out/\">放弃了出售计划</a>，接下来如何，就要看 <a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/2013/11/04/blackberry-interim-ceo-plans-to-keep-making-smartphones/\">Thorsten Heins 接班人</a>的了。<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n经由：<a href=\"http://www.engadget.com/2013/11/05/canadian-government-blocked-potential-lenovo-bid-for-blackberry/\">Engadget</a><br />\n引用来源：<a href=\"http://www.theglobeandmail.com/report-on-business/international-business/asian-pacific-business/lenovo-considered-a-bid-for-blackberry-but-ottawa-wouldnt-accept-chinese-takeover/article15256976/?cmpid=rss1&amp;click=dlvr.it\" target=\"_blank\">The Globe and Mail</a></div><p><h6 style=\"clear: both; padding: 8px 0 0 0; height: 2px; font-size: 1px; border: 0; margin: 0; padding: 0;\"></h6><a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/2013/11/05/canadian-government-blocked-potential-lenovo-bid-for-blackberry/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent link to this entry\">此文章网址</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/forward/20761686/\" title=\"Send this entry to a friend via email\">转寄此文章</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/2013/11/05/canadian-government-blocked-potential-lenovo-bid-for-blackberry/#comments\" title=\"View reader comments on this entry\">回应</a><hr size=\"1\" />", 
